  {
    "header": {
      "appName": "E:D Black Box",
      "appVersion": "1.0",
      "appURL": "https://github.com/tusharsaxena/ed-blackbox",
      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "mining",
          "intro": "A large-pad volume-mining fit that turns the Caspian's deep internals into a ~276 t ore hold while keeping a real gun and a light bi-weave for self-defence. Initial is buy-only; A-rated is the mining baseline; Engineered adds range, cool running and shield the tools themselves stay stock, since mining hardware is not engineerable. This is a re-roled explorer, not a purpose-built barge: it hauls a respectable hold but carries no mining hull bonus and lands large-pad only.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Full suite, mid-pack hold",
            "text": "The hull mounts the complete kit — twin lasers, a seismic launcher, abrasion blaster and sub-surface missile for both laser and core work, a Pulse Wave Analyser to find rocks, a 4A refinery and three collector controllers — plus a large multi-cannon that most miners can't spare a mount for. The limit is the hold: with shield, scoop and the mining suite fitted you keep roughly 276 t of ore, short of a Type-9 (~790 t) or Anaconda (~470 t max), on a ~189M Cr hull that only ever docks large."
          },
          "notes": {
            "Armour": "Mk II Ablative Military Grade bulkheads, Heavy Duty plus Deep Plating — a laden miner is a static target, so hardening the hull buys the seconds needed to boost clear of a pirate.",
            "LargeHardpoint1": "Large gimballed multi-cannon for genuine self-defence, not just deterrence; Overcharged plus Corrosive Shell let it actually kill an interdictor rather than only scaring one off — an edge most miners lack a mount for.",
            "MediumHardpoint1": "The primary mining laser; a fixed medium laser does the bulk of surface-deposit cutting, and mining lasers carry no weapon blueprint.",
            "MediumHardpoint2": "A second medium mining laser doubles laser-mining throughput on a prospected rock; not engineerable.",
            "MediumHardpoint3": "Core mining's crack tool lob a seismic charge into a fissure to split the rock; medium fixed warhead, and mining tools aren't engineerable.",
            "MediumHardpoint4": "Abrasion Blaster shears surface deposits off a cracked core for the limpets to scoop; no blueprint applies to mining tools.",
            "MediumHardpoint5": "Sub-surface Displacement Missile reaches the deep deposits the blaster can't; mining missiles carry no blueprint.",
            "MediumHardpoint6": "Second, smaller gimballed multi-cannon; Overcharged plus Auto Loader keep it firing through a sustained defence without reloading.",
            "TinyHardpoint1": "Pulse Wave Analyser lights up mineral-rich rocks and core fissures; held at class 3 to spare the power budget, and scanners carry no blueprint.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "First of three Heavy-Duty boosters; each multiplies the light bi-weave's raw MJ the cheapest survivability on the hull.",
            "TinyHardpoint3": "Second Heavy-Duty booster stiffens the shield for the exposed minutes cracking a core.",
            "TinyHardpoint4": "Third Heavy-Duty booster; diminishing returns set in but the shield is the primary defence, so it still pays.",
            "TinyHardpoint5": "Optional / low-priority Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and cool scooping.",
            "TinyHardpoint6": "Second heat-sink launcher; a second charge bank means you never run dry mid-escape.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rate it to run twin lasers, the seismic launcher and the limpet swarm together; Low Emissions plus Thermal Spread hold heat down through long sessions.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rated size-7 thrusters with Dirty Drive Tuning plus Drag Drives so a 950 t hull can boost clear of an interdiction it can't out-fight.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "The class-8 SCO drive is the Caspian's calling card; Increased Range plus Mass Manager stretch every jump so it reaches distant pristine rings other miners slog out to.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rated and Lightweight life support is mass to shed on a miner, and it has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "A-rate the class-7 distributor or the lasers and limpets brown out together; Weapon Focused feeds the WEP capacitor that runs the mining lasers continuously.",
            "Radar": "Dropped to D and Lightweight a miner needs no sensor range, so save the mass; sensors have no experimental effect.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock class-7 tank for long legs to distant rings; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size7": "Largest ore rack the hold's core; cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot02_Size6": "A size-6 bi-weave is the practical shield here; Reinforced plus Hi-Cap maximise MJ while keeping the quick recharge enough to survive a clumsy rock or buy an escape, not to brawl.",
            "Slot03_Size6": "Second big ore rack. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot04_Size5": "Ore rack. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot05_Size5": "Ore rack. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot06_Size5": "Fuel scoop for self-sufficiency reaching distant pristine rings; scoop rate is fixed and not engineerable.",
            "Slot07_Size5": "Primary collector limpet controller; Lightweight trims its mass. Deploys the bulk of the collector swarm.",
            "Slot08_Size4": "4A refinery the largest the hull mounts, with the most bins; Shielded hardens it. Processes mined fragments.",
            "Slot09_Size4": "Ore rack. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot10_Size3": "Second collector controller for a larger simultaneous limpet swarm; Lightweight trims its mass.",
            "Slot11_Size2": "Small ore rack topping off the hold. Cargo racks aren't engineerable.",
            "Slot12_Size1": "Prospector limpet controller; Lightweight trims its mass. Prospectors read a rock's yield before you commit the lasers.",
            "Slot13_Size1": "Detailed Surface Scanner maps ring hotspots (and planets for spare cartographic data); Expanded Probe Scanning widens probe coverage.",
            "Slot14_Size1": "Third collector controller so the swarm keeps pace with two lasers; Lightweight trims its mass."
          },
          "engineeringPlan": [
